1 A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
2 AN ACT DECRIMINALIZING POSSESSION OF FIVE GRAMS OR LESS OF
3 MARIJUANA; CONFORMING THE STATE DEFINITION OF HEMP WITH THE
4 FEDERAL DEFINITION AND PROHIBITING CERTAIN THC AND CANNABIS
5 PRODUCTS; INCREASING THE PENALTIES FOR MANUFACTURING AND
6 SELLING MARIJUANA; RAISING THE AGE TO PURCHASE TOBACCO, VAPOR,
7 AND CONSUMABLE PRODUCTS; INCREASING THE EXCISE TAX ON VAPOR
8 PRODUCTS; INCREASING THE UNAUTHORIZED SUBSTANCE EXCISE TAX ON
9 MARIJUANA; EXPANDING ALCOHOL LAW ENFORCEMENT'S (ALE) SUBJECT
10 MATTER JURISDICTION; MAKING AN APPROPRIATION FOR EVIDENCE
11 STORAGE AND DISPOSAL BY ALE; AND MAKING ADMINISTRATIVE AND
12 ENFORCEMENT CHANGES TO THE VAPOR PRODUCTS DIRECTORY.
